window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>A classic Marple mystery, read by Emilia Fox.&nbsp;</p> <p>For an instant the two trains ran together, side by side. In that frozen moment, Elspeth witnessed a murder. Helplessly, she stared out of her carriage window as a man remorselessly tightened his grip around a woman's throat. The body crumpled. Then the other train drew away. But who, apart from Miss Marple, would take her story seriously? After all, there were no suspects, no other witnessesâ€¦ and no corpse.</p>"; 
